## 5. INLINE COMMENTING

### Inline Arrows
**Inline Comments**
- Use `// <-- Comment` for explanatory comments in JavaScript
- Use `# <-- Comment` for explanatory comments in Python
- Use `/* <-- Comment */` for explanatory comments in CSS
- Always on the same line as the code, directly after the item being described
- Do not place comments on a separate line above or below unless absolutely necessary
- One quick phrase or note; avoid full sentences unless clarification is essential
- "Columnise" by aligning the comments vertically when there are multiple related lines

```comment_example.js
    // SUB FUNCTION | Update Project Configuration
    // ------------------------------------------------------------
    function updateProjectConfig(project, updates) {
        project.projectName = updates.name || project.projectName;          // <-- Set new name
        project.projectCode = updates.code || project.projectCode;          // <-- Set new code
        project.description = updates.description || project.description;    // <-- Set new description
        
        const metadata = project.metadata || {};                             // Get metadata object
        metadata.lastUpdated = new Date().toISOString();                     // Update timestamp
        project.metadata = metadata;                                         // Save updated metadata
    }
    // ---------------------------------------------------------------
```

